title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\RouterNatSubnetworkToNat
name: RouterNatSubnetworkToNat
description:
Defines the IP ranges that want to use NAT for a subnetwork.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.RouterNatSubnetworkToNat

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data.name
params.description: URL for the subnetwork resource that will use NAT.

params.name: data.secondary_ip_range_names
params.description: A list of the secondary ranges of the Subnetwork that are allowed to use NAT. This can be populated only if "LIST_OF_SECONDARY_IP_RANGES" is one of the values in source_ip_ranges_to_nat.

params.name: data.source_ip_ranges_to_nat
params.description: Specify the options for NAT ranges in the Subnetwork. All options of a single value are valid except NAT_IP_RANGE_OPTION_UNSPECIFIED. The only valid option with multiple values is: ["PRIMARY_IP_RANGE", "LIST_OF_SECONDARY_IP_RANGES"] Default: [ALL_IP_RANGES] Check the SourceIpRangesToNat enum for the list of possible values.
